All Implemented Interfaces:

public final class DynamicLoader extends URLClassLoader
An instance of this class is a custom class-loader that can load a compiled Autumn program.

    • invokeMain

      public void invokeMain(String[] args) throws ClassNotFoundException, NoSuchMethodException, InvocationTargetException, IllegalAccessException
      This method invokes the program's entry-point thereby causing the program to execute.

      This method does fails quietly, if the program's entry-point was not specified.

      Parameters:
      args - are the arguments to pass to the main method.
      Throws:
      ClassNotFoundException - if the main class does not exist.
      NoSuchMethodException - if the main method does not exist.
      InvocationTargetException - if main method throws an exception.
      IllegalAccessException - if the main method cannot be accessed reflectively.
